Desmodium velutinum

    Authority
      Family
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5267

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: Erect or semi-erect shrub or sub-shrub, up to 3 m high.
   Leaves 1-foliolate, rarely 3-foliolate, 4-20 cm long and 2.5-13 cm
   wide. Flowers purple to pink. Pods narrowly oblong, 1-2.5 cm long, 2-3
   mm wide. USE: Used in cut-and-carry or permanently grazed systems.
   GROWING PERIOD: Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Desmodium. FURTHER INF: It is
   native of tropical Asia and Africa where it is found at altitudes from
   0-1500 m, with average temperature above 20ÂºC. It prefers humid
   climates of more than 1000-4000 mm annual rainfall. However, tolerates
   up to 5 months dry season. Adapted to a wide range of soil pH, from
   very acid (pH 4.0) to alkaline. Adapted to low-fertility soils.

   Sources
   Tropical forages 2005

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
